        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I add the dbAdapter into session to avoid initializing it for every request.\r\nI have the code below in my bootstrap file\r\n\r\nif(empty($ns->dbAdapter)) {\r\n    $ns = new Zend_Session_Namespace('test');\r\n    $ns->dbAdapter = Zend_Db::factory($config->db->adapter, $config->db->config->toArray());\r\n}\r\n$ns->dbAdapter->setFetchMode(Zend_Db::FETCH_OBJ);\r\nZend_Db_Table::setDefaultAdapter($ns->dbAdapter);\r\n\r\nSometimes (about 1 click out of 10), an exception is thrown when I start a new request:\r\n\r\nYou cannot serialize or unserialize PDO instances\r\n#0. File:\r\nC:\\Data\\websites\\xyz\\library\\Zend\\Session.php\r\nLine: 480\r\n"
        },
